Description: 9 body sherds of Nubian coarse ware, all hand-made and all from different vessels. All of them are decorated at the outside in either parallel lines or basketry impression. All of them have separate numbers on them: A: AWS 52, AW 38/39, X, eroded, incised lines on outer surface. B: AWS 193, very eroded on both sides, probably originally basketry pattern outside. C: AWS 194, basketry pattern outside. D: AWS 204, incised lines. E: AWS 529, incised dashed lines. F: AW 38/39, X, Am P.5, Temple X, basketry impression. G: AW 38/39, X, Am P.6, eroded, originally probably basketry. H: AW 38/39, X, Am P.10, fine dotted lines. I: AW 38/39, X, Am P. 11, fine and polished inside, dotted lines, very likely to be from the same vessel as H.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
